Library Project - Jimmy Kurian - 2/18/2012
Written in HTML 4.01, XHTML 1.0, CSS 2.1, and JavaScript 1.8.5
Written using Ruby 1.9.3-p0, Rails 3.2.1, and SQLite 3.7.10

The Library Project is a Rails project for managing books and authors and supporting a many-to-many relationship between them. 
The book table has the fields: title (string), publication date (date), length in pages (integer), and language (must be English, 
French, Spanish, or German).  The author table has the fields: first name (string), last name (string), birth date (date), birth city (string), 
birth country (string). 

To run the project, using Command Prompt, do to the directory where the project is located. Run the command "rails s" and wait for the the web server
to boot up. After it has booted up, open a new window in internet browser, like Mozilla Firefox, and then enter the URL: http://localhost:3000/index

You should be able to view the project now. 

*NOTE: You must have the version of Ruby, Rails, and SQLite used to write this project to run this project properly.